§I HYPOTHESIS-TO-FALSIFY
  H · cssl-ast/src/diagnostic.rs can be extended to render rustc-quality diagnostics :
       file:line:col · source-line snippet · caret pointing at offending span ·
       did-you-mean suggestion (edit-distance ≤ 2) · ANSI color when stderr is tty
       without breaking any existing diagnostic call-site

§I FAILURE-MODE-ENUMERATION
  FM.1 · diagnostic.rs may be the SOLE file but call-sites may be MANY (1775 .rs files)
         changing Diagnostic struct shape = mass rewrites
         mitigation : keep existing constructors · ADD new render() path · preserve API

  FM.2 · A89.3 ANSI color when tty · cargo build redirects stderr → no-tty
         BUT humans want color in interactive csslc compile · use atty crate or
         std::io::IsTerminal (Rust 1.70+) · check stderr only · respect NO_COLOR env
         per https://no-color.org

  FM.3 · A89.2 "did you mean" via edit-distance can produce false-positives
         (e.g. `let x = y` typo'd to `let x = z` · BOTH might be defined symbols)
         mitigation : suggest only when single-best within edit-distance ≤ 2 · else silent
         + threshold by symbol-similarity (kind-aware : variable vs type vs fn)

  FM.4 · source-snippet rendering needs file-content access · diagnostic system
         currently may not have file-access (just span : path + offset)
         mitigation : add SourceMap or file-cache · OR re-read file on diagnostic emit
                       (slow but simple · acceptable for compile-error path)

  FM.5 · multi-line spans · spans-across-macro-expansion · Unicode width counting
         (non-ASCII chars take varying terminal width)
         mitigation : Phase-1 = ASCII single-line spans only · OQ for multi-line/Unicode

  FM.6 · color codes leaking into log files · CI logs · GitHub Actions output
         mitigation : strict tty-only check · NO_COLOR env override · CLICOLOR_FORCE override

§I CHEAPEST-FALSIFICATION
  fixture : examples/diag_test.cssl with deliberate type-mismatch
  invoke : csslc compile examples/diag_test.cssl 2>&1
  expect output shape :
    error[T0001]: expected `i64`, got `u32`
      --> examples/diag_test.cssl:3:23
       |
     3 | fn f(x : u32) -> i64 { x }
       |                       ^ this is `u32`, not `i64`
       |
       = help: try explicit cast : `x as i64`
  if any line missing · A89.* unmet
  ⇒ snapshot-test pattern · ~20 LOC · highest-signal

